60|$|Kit, all bluff and {{hardened}} {{with the}} cold, went on manfully; and, having {{enough to do}} to keep his blood circulating, to picture to himself the happy end of this adventurous journey, and to look about him and <b>be</b> <b>amazed</b> <b>at</b> everything, had little spare time for thinking of discomforts. Though his impatience, and that of his fellow-travellers, rapidly increased as the day waned, the hours did not stand still. The short daylight of winter soon faded away, and it was dark again when they had yet many miles to travel.|$|E
